canonical:
  title: 又與翰林阮爲太尉王請諡書
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以聖朝功臣世家例得贈謚而先太尉瀋王薨逝逾年尙未擧行今具表文啓省上聞外念先王歷事六朝實多勞績累被天奬元臣懿戚無有不知若蒙平生行跡得列華藻以示將來則先王可爲死而不死其於存歿爲榮莫大伏惟照審不宣
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 又與翰林阮爲太尉王請諡書
  author: 崔瀣
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以聖朝功臣世家。例得贈謚。而先太尉瀋王薨逝逾年。尙未擧行。今具表文。啓省上聞。外念先王歷事六朝。實多勞績。累被天奬。元臣懿戚。無有不知。若蒙平生行跡。得列華藻。以示將來。則先王可爲死而不死。其於存歿。爲榮莫大。伏惟照審。不宣。
korean:
  title: 우여 한림원 위태위 왕청시 서
  author: 최해
  language: kor
  text: 성조(聖朝)의 공신 세가(世家)는 전례대로 시호(諡號)를 내리심을 받았으나, 선태위(先太尉) 심왕(瀋王)은 돌아가신 지 해가 넘었는데도 아직 거행치 않으므로 이제 표문을 갖추어 임금께서 들으시도록 아룁니다. 밖에서 생각하건대, 선왕은 여섯 조정을 대대로 섬겨 애써 세운 공적이 참으로 많아 누차 천자의 칭찬을 받았음은 대신과 왕실의 가깝고 친밀한 외척으로 모르는 사람이 없습니다. 만약 평생의 행적으로 빛나는 글을 얻어 장래에 나타나게 된다면, 선왕은 돌아가셨어도 돌아가시지 않은 것이 될 수 있어 그 존망(存亡)에 있어서 영광됨이 이보다 클 수 없습니다. 분명히 살피시기를 엎드려 바라오며, 다 말씀드리지 못합니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0650_010_0090&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Requesting a Posthumous Title for General Wang, Composed with Scholar Acolyte Won
  author: Choe Hae
  language: eng
  text: Humbly I observe that the eminent ministers and noble families of our sagacious court receive, by precedent, posthumous titles upon their passing. Yet the late General, the Prince of Shen, departed more than a year ago, and still this honor has not been bestowed. Now I present this memorial, that it may reach the sovereign's ear. Reflecting upon it, the late Prince served six successive dynasties with distinguished achievement and toil. Repeatedly did Heaven's favor shine upon him—a truth known to all, whether among the high ministers or the imperial kinsmen. Should his lifetime of deeds be adorned with the brilliant characters of his name in perpetuity, then the late Prince shall live on eternally beyond death itself. No greater honor could be granted between the living and the departed. I humbly beg Your Majesty's careful consideration. What remains is unspoken.
  footnotes:
    - This is a formal memorial requesting imperial recognition through the bestowal of a posthumous name (posthumous title), a traditional honor for those of rank and virtue.
    - The 'six successive dynasties' likely refers to the tumultuous period of Korean history when multiple kingdoms and dynasties held power, suggesting the late Prince's long and consistent service through many political transitions.
